<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-17T17:14:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-17T17:14:00-05:00" n="343" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d343">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/798.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hartman</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-17T17:00:00-05:14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1915—5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s June 16, 10 a.m. I presented matter unofficially today. The
                            Minister for Foreign Affairs regrets inability to make remittance now.
                            He says that high officials and subordinate officers of the Government
                            have not been paid since January and that the Government has not been
                            able to pay the army promptly. Income from import duties very slight
                            since European war.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>